<h2> Definition </h2>

<p>
<strong>@HI{{niyotte}}</strong>, in this construction, indicates that the preceding noun is the cause of the subsequent
clause.

<table class="sentence">
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{uchino@KJ{{craft^location}}deha,@KJ{{lumber^fee^negative^leg}}<strong>niyotte</strong>
      tatamino@KJ{{life^products}}hamoudekinakatta.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      In our factory, because of the shortage of materials, no more tatami can be produced.
  </td> </tr>
</table>
</p>

<p>
<strong>@HI{{niyotte}}</strong>, can also mean "by using the method of".
clause.

<table class="sentence">
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{@KJ{{outside^country^word}}wo@KJ{{study}}bukoto<strong>niyotte</strong>sono@KJ{{country}}no@KJ{{person}}tachi
      no@KJ{{consider}}e@KJ{{direction}}mo@KJ{{know}}rukotogadekiru.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      Through foreign language study, one can understand how people from that country think.
  </td> </tr>
</table>
</p>

